TOUGH GAME
       02.07.16

Cam Newton Mopes, Ditches Post-Game Presser
       Cam Newton
       NFL Network
       Carolina Panthers quarterback Cam Newton was understandably
       miserable after losing Super Bowl 50 to the Denver Broncos on
       Sunday evening. During a post-game presser, the young star appeared
       dejected and untalkative, giving terse responses to questions about
       his team's poor performance. “I don't know what you want me to say,
       I'm sorry," he said, eventually walking off the stage and abruptly
       ending the press conference.

     "I don’t know what you want me to say, I’m sorry." - A dejected Cam
     Newton walks off the podium abruptly. [9]#SB50
     [10]https://t.co/xw4iLd1CQz
     — NFL (@NFL) [11]February 8, 2016
